Sentencas: Aerosol-assisted metal-organic chemical vapor deposition (AA-MOCVD) with beta-diketonate precursors was employed in depositing thin films of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) electrolyte material, gadolinia-doped ceria (GDC), on anode (NiO + YSZ) substrates.
Titulo: Aerosol-assisted MOCVD growth of Gd2O3-doped CeO2 thin SOFC electrolyte film on anode substrate

Sentencas: The films have been successfully synthesized in a wide temperature range (300-600 degreesC) and characterized by X-ray powder diffraction, scanning electron microscopy (SEM) and X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy (XPS).
Titulo: Aerosol-assisted MOCVD growth of Gd2O3-doped CeO2 thin SOFC electrolyte film on anode substrate

Sentencas: The sheet resistance measurements were carried out between 350 and 850 degreesC to study the effects of adsorbed oxygen on film ionic conductivity.
Titulo: Aerosol-assisted MOCVD growth of Gd2O3-doped CeO2 thin SOFC electrolyte film on anode substrate
